<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com/maintenance-release-for-the-week-of-19-november-2017/">Maintenance Release for the Week of 19 November 2017</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://theeventscalendar.com">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>
";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Neill";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5527:"<p>Welcome to Maintenance Release number 23 of 2017! Here are some fixes and tweaks for you, to help your plugins run more smoothly. If this is your first time getting an update from us remember Maintenance Releases are smaller updates between major releases that are mostly comprised of bug Fixes, tweaks, and small but meaningful improvements. We always recommend using a staging site to test these changes before updating on a live site.</p>
<p>To see all of the changes included this Maintenance Release, check out the changelogs for all updated plugins below:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#tec">The Events Calendar 4.6.6</a></li>
<li><a href="#ce">Community Events 4.5.8</a></li>
<li><a href="#ct">Community Tickets 4.5.2</a></li>
<li><a href="#et">Event Tickets 4.6.1</a></li>
<li><a href="#etp">Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1</a></li>
<li><a href="#not-updated">Not Updated This Release</a></li>
</ul>
<h3 id="tec">The Events Calendar 4.6.6</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Feature</strong> &#8211; Added Template class which adds a few layers of filtering to any template file included</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Add clear warnings and errors to prevent and limit the import of iCalendar sources missing required fields</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Included `tribe_callback_return` for static returns for Hooks</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Improve Aggregator notices including error data on the responses</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="ce">Community Events 4.5.8</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Only display admin links in Community Tickets if user is able to access the admin</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="ct">Community Tickets 4.5.2</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Fix New Ticket and New RSVP alignment </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Only display admin links in Community Tickets if user is able to access the admin </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Changed views: `community-tickets/modules/tickets`</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="et">Event Tickets 4.6.1</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevents unnecessary AJAX requests when using tickets editor </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removes weird clearing of fields when canceling or saving Tickets </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Allow saving of Ticket Editor contents when Updating the Event </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Included more hooks via the new Template class for the Ticket Editor: `tribe_template_file`, `tribe_template_before_include`, `tribe_template_after_include` and `tribe_template_html` </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Only display admin links in Community Tickets if user is able to access the admin </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; spacing of message to logged in users to view attendees </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; RSVP and Tickets migration from pre-4.6 updates capacity corretly for all cases now (props to Uwe Matern) </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Attendees column for events display correctly the percentages now </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Tickets Editor now has more support for Accessibility </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filters: `tribe_ticket_filter_attendee_report_link`, `tribe_tickets_attendees_show_title`</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed filters: `tribe_tickets_default_end_date`, `tribe_tickets_ajax_refresh_settings`, `tribe_tickets_can_update_ticket_price`, `tribe_tickets_disallow_update_ticket_price_message`, `tribe_events_tickets_metabox_edit_attendee`</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added actions: `tribe_tickets_save_post`</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed actions: `tribe_events_tickets_pre_ticket_list`, `tribe_events_tickets_post_ticket_list`</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Changed views: `tickets/email`, `tickets/orders-link`</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="etp">Event Tickets Plus 4.6.1</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; EDD quantity styling to match WooCommerce and RSVP forms </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Only display admin links in Community Tickets if user is able to access the admin </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Add checkin status class to EDD to fix checkin button&#8217;s showing as disabled </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Formats properly when displaying Unlimited capacity Tickets </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Prevents deleted shared event capacity to still factor in when no tickets are sharing capacity </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Updating capacity for the event all tickets gets Stock validation preventing Out of Stock message </li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Added filters: `tribe_events_tickets_edd_display_ecommerce_links`, `tribe_filter_attendee_order_link`</li>
<li><strong>Tweak</strong> &#8211; Removed filters: `tribe_events_tickets_woo_display_ecommerce_links`</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="not-updated">Not Updated This Release</h3>
<p>The following plugins have not been updated this release and will remain at the version numbers specified here:</p>
<ul>
<li>Events Calendar PRO 4.4.19</li>
<li>Filter Bar 4.5.1</li>
<li>Image Widget 4.4.7</li>
<li>Advanced Post Manager 4.4</li>
<li>Eventbrite Tickets 4.4.8</li>
<li>Image Widget Plus 1.0.2</li>
<li>GigPress 2.3.19</li>
</ul>
